sentences: Johan Petter Krafman better known by his stage name Midnight Boy (born 6 April 1988 in Helsingborg, Sweden) is a Swedish singer and songwriter.
Johan Petter Krafman better known by his stage name Midnight Boy (born 6 April 1988 in Helsingborg, Sweden) is a Swedish singer and songwriter.
His music is strongly inspired by 1980s electropop and rock.
Krafman's career started in the summer of 2008 when he participated in the talent show Artistjakten by Mix Megapol, a Swedish national radio station.

He also performed at the Ladies Night shows in Stockholm, Gothenburg and Malm√∂ with the singer Martin Stenmarck, actor Peter Stormare and comedian Henrik Hjelt.
In connection with the Ladies Night tour he released two songs called "Disarmed" and "Chain Reaction" under his regular name.
In 2013, Midnight Boy released the single "Roll With It" using his newly adopted stage name.
The song took Midnight Boy to a mini tour to United States, where he performed at the Avalon club in Los Angeles.

Also in 2013, Midnight Boy released the single "When You're Strange" with a controversial music video, where he took off all of his clothes at Stureplan with the slogan "When naked, there is no difference".
Midnight Boy participated in the fourth semifinal of Melodifestivalen 2015 with the song "Don't Say No".
